cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper describes a system for monitoring network traffic and detecting anomalies, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The primary focus is on network infrastructure (cs.NI), as the system is designed to monitor network traffic and detect anomalies in real-time. The paper also discusses security (cs.CR) and distributed systems (cs.DC), as the system is designed to be scalable and able to handle large amounts of data. Additionally, the system could be applied to control systems (cs.SY) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) for analyzing and processing the collected data.
